Look at this.

10:23.190 --> 10:25.159
Cooper was on a WaveRunner
having fun without me.

10:25.192 --> 10:26.159
Look at this.

10:26.192 --> 10:27.461
Right now your dad is at a party.

10:27.494 --> 10:29.363
Having fun without me.

10:29.395 --> 10:31.698
I can't stop looking at my phone.

10:31.731 --> 10:34.467
Now I know what you guys go
through with social media.

10:34.500 --> 10:36.202
Makes you feel like a loser, doesn't it?

10:36.235 --> 10:37.970
- We <i> are</i> losers.
- Total losers.

10:38.004 --> 10:39.773
We're garbage, human garbage.

10:39.806 --> 10:40.974
We should crawl into a dumpster.

10:41.007 --> 10:43.143
- And curl up and die.
- Yeah.

10:44.878 --> 10:46.747
Maybe you and I shouldn't be
around each other right now.

10:48.714 --> 10:49.817
Trip!

10:49.850 --> 10:51.451
I didn't know you were over.

10:51.485 --> 10:52.820
I'm so happy to see you.

10:52.852 --> 10:54.520
Wow, Mrs. A.

10:54.553 --> 10:56.622
I haven't been hugged like this
since I told my English teacher

10:56.656 --> 10:57.558
I was dropping his class.

10:57.591 --> 10:59.960
Mom, don't be weird.

10:59.993 --> 11:02.830
So, Dad is out again with
his new best friend Dane.

11:02.863 --> 11:05.898
Whatever. Who needs Dad? Not me.

11:05.932 --> 11:08.067
I have you guys. What are you doing?

11:08.100 --> 11:10.037
I have to observe the meteor
shower for homework,

11:10.070 --> 11:11.071
and Trip said he'd keep me company.

11:11.104 --> 11:13.240
- I'm in.
- I didn't invite you.

11:13.273 --> 11:15.875
Well, I didn't mean to have you,
so now we're even.

11:21.081 --> 11:22.582
Oh, wait. Meteor shower.

11:22.615 --> 11:24.217
Better grab an umbrella.

11:24.250 --> 11:25.418
Always thinking.

11:27.421 --> 11:28.989
You shall not destroy me!

11:29.022 --> 11:30.190
Show me what you got!

11:31.424 --> 11:32.992
What are you guys doing?

11:33.025 --> 11:34.594
Mom already tried to crash our playdate.

11:34.628 --> 11:35.929
Find your own friend.

11:35.961 --> 11:37.163
I don't have a friend.

11:37.196 --> 11:39.365
Yes, you do. Go talk to Cooper.

11:39.398 --> 11:41.835
What happened to Cooper...
Cooper the Pooper.

11:41.868 --> 11:43.771
Genius.

11:43.803 --> 11:45.505
He lied to me about his plans

11:45.538 --> 11:48.241
so he could go to a yacht party
without me last weekend.

11:48.274 --> 11:49.442
That's not last weekend.

11:49.475 --> 11:50.844
What are you talking about?

11:50.876 --> 11:53.246
Look... Those are Fourth
of July napkins.

11:53.279 --> 11:54.847
How did you even notice that?

11:54.880 --> 11:57.617
- I love themed napkins.
- He really does.

11:57.650 --> 11:59.419
It makes Christmas shopping a breeze.

11:59.452 --> 12:01.587
It is the Fourth of July.

12:01.620 --> 12:03.756
Why would Cooper lie to me
and post an old photo?

12:03.789 --> 12:05.291
Go talk to him and find out.

12:05.325 --> 12:06.560
I think I will.

12:06.592 --> 12:07.727
Thanks, Franklin.

12:10.897 --> 12:12.766
- What?
- It's not you.

12:12.798 --> 12:15.601
It's just when a woman
has an idea, he ignores it,

12:15.634 --> 12:19.639
but when a man says the same
thing, he's suddenly all ears.

12:21.408 --> 12:22.609
I wish I was all ears.

12:22.642 --> 12:24.812
Stupid nose.

12:28.281 --> 12:29.917
Sorry we haven't seen anything yet.

12:29.950 --> 12:31.451
Ah, don't worry about it.

12:31.485 --> 12:33.887
I could stay out here
all night with you.

12:33.919 --> 12:36.589
I've got Bugles. I've got Combos.

12:36.623 --> 12:37.758
I've got Chicken In A Biskit.

12:37.791 --> 12:38.926
Ooh, Chicken In A Biskit!

12:38.959 --> 12:40.494
Mom, you really don't need to be here.

12:41.695 --> 12:43.297
Look! There's a meteor!

12:43.330 --> 12:46.233
- Wow!
- No, wait. That's a plane.

12:46.265 --> 12:48.134
- A shooting star!
- Wow!

12:48.168 --> 12:50.269
Nope! Another plane.

12:53.172 --> 12:54.575
Is that Doris or Angela?

12:54.608 --> 12:55.976
It's probably an emergency.

12:56.009 --> 12:57.344
No time to take it, just go.

12:57.376 --> 12:58.744
Dane just put up more photos

12:58.778 --> 13:01.081
of him and your dad at the 1799 party.

13:01.114 --> 13:02.682
They're assembling muskets,

13:02.716 --> 13:04.784
cobbling shoes,
and churning butter together.

13:04.817 --> 13:06.352
That stuff's so cool.

13:06.385 --> 13:08.988
Your generation was so lucky
you got to do all that.

13:11.191 --> 13:13.460
Look at how your dad is smiling at Dane.

13:13.493 --> 13:15.028
Look at how much fun they're having.

13:15.061 --> 13:17.663
He should be having fun with me.

13:17.696 --> 13:19.131
You need to go down there and show him

13:19.164 --> 13:21.367
you are way more fun than Dane.

13:21.400 --> 13:23.202
- You think I should?
- Absolutely.

13:23.235 --> 13:25.639
You need to let Dane know
he's the third wheel.

13:25.672 --> 13:28.307
You know, somebody who wants
to hang out with a couple

13:28.341 --> 13:30.177
when the couple really
wants to be left alone.

13:32.913 --> 13:35.115
- I can take a hint.
- No, no, no! Not you!

13:55.268 --> 13:57.704
Hey, Katie. What are you doing here?

13:57.736 --> 14:02.308
I am reliving the past
with an eye towards the future.

14:02.341 --> 14:03.910
Oh, my God. Katie, thank you

14:03.943 --> 14:05.211
for paying attention
to the Guild's mission.

14:05.244 --> 14:07.214
Of course. I listen.

14:07.246 --> 14:08.481
Where's Dane?

14:08.514 --> 14:09.850
He's at the mead pong table.

14:12.851 --> 14:14.887
He's dominating. No one can beat him.

14:14.921 --> 14:16.089
He's so cool.

14:16.121 --> 14:18.091
You think dominating beer pong is cool?

14:18.124 --> 14:19.359
Great.

14:19.392 --> 14:20.661
I will be back.

14:20.693 --> 14:22.328
<i>I'm from Florida.</i>

14:22.361 --> 14:24.497
<i>They teach beer pong in school
as an elective.</i>

14:24.531 --> 14:25.935
<i>Hmm.</i>

14:27.200 --> 14:28.602
Hey.

14:34.640 --> 14:36.776
Hey, Katie, you made it. Great!

14:36.810 --> 14:39.780
We'll see how great you think
it is once your reign is over.

14:41.781 --> 14:43.050
Ye on.

14:50.050 --> 14:51.113
I'm dominating.

14:56.015 --> 14:57.866
Drink! Drink! Drink! Drink!

14:57.891 --> 14:59.069
Drink! Drink!

15:04.169 --> 15:05.839
Suck a musket, Dane.

15:10.677 --> 15:13.747
Yeah! Whoo!

15:21.488 --> 15:23.345
Drink, drink, drink!

15:23.370 --> 15:25.292
Drink, drink, drink!

15:25.325 --> 15:29.821
Drink, drink, drink, drink,
drink, drink, drink, drink!

15:42.475 --> 15:45.144
Yeah! In your face!

15:45.177 --> 15:46.413
C'mon, everybody...

15:46.446 --> 15:48.850
Dane sucks! Dane sucks!

15:48.936 --> 15:51.183
- Dane sucks! Dane sucks!
- Dane sucks! Dane sucks!

15:51.216 --> 15:53.285
- Dane sucks! Dane sucks!
- Dane sucks! Dane...

15:53.318 --> 15:55.755
Katie, could I speak to you
by the stocks, please?

15:55.788 --> 15:57.357
Yeah.

15:59.459 --> 16:01.328
How is this fun for you?

16:01.360 --> 16:04.130
It's not. My cellphone rang
during a re-enactment.

16:04.163 --> 16:05.365
It was the third time.

16:05.398 --> 16:07.267
I hate nerds so much.

16:07.299 --> 16:09.268
What was that all about?

16:09.302 --> 16:12.139
I don't want you doing all this
stuff with Dane every night.

16:12.172 --> 16:13.507
You encouraged me
to be friends with him.

16:13.539 --> 16:14.707
Well, that was stupid.

16:14.740 --> 16:17.276
And it takes up too much of your time.

16:17.310 --> 16:18.645
You're jealous.

16:18.677 --> 16:20.179
That's amazing.

16:20.212 --> 16:22.348
I should have gotten
a new friend years ago.

16:22.382 --> 16:25.218
I just... miss you.

16:25.250 --> 16:26.986
I wanted you to find a new friend,

16:27.019 --> 16:28.388
but not a new best friend.

16:28.421 --> 16:30.290
I'm supposed to be your best friend.

16:30.322 --> 16:33.459
Sweetie, I like Dane, but you
will always be my best friend.

16:33.493 --> 16:35.595
You're hands-down my favorite
person to do stuff with.

16:36.663 --> 16:38.230
- Really?
- Of course.

16:38.264 --> 16:40.167
I'm sorry I ever made you doubt that.

16:40.200 --> 16:42.169
And to prove it, I'll take
you out for a fun night.

16:42.201 --> 16:44.037
- I'd like that.
- Done.

16:44.070 --> 16:46.039
You know, next week is the unveiling

16:46.071 --> 16:47.474
of the Wesley Lyon headstone restoration

16:47.507 --> 16:48.542
at the Willowbrook Cemetery.

16:48.575 --> 16:49.710
You can do that with Dane.

16:57.884 --> 16:59.485
Could somebody give me a hand?!

17:06.592 --> 17:08.561
Hey, Chambers let me in.

17:11.964 --> 17:15.267
Please have Chambers
reassigned to the bowling alley...

17:15.300 --> 17:16.736
shoe rentals.

17:18.404 --> 17:20.373
Didn't know you had
an arcade in your basement.

17:20.406 --> 17:22.443
In the winter it's an ice-skating rink.

17:23.642 --> 17:25.578
Oh, yeah.

17:25.611 --> 17:27.613
So what you want?

17:27.646 --> 17:30.082
I just wanted to say I was sorry.

17:30.116 --> 17:32.719
I was mad because I thought
you blew me off.

17:32.752 --> 17:34.053
Why would you think that?

17:34.087 --> 17:35.522
Because when I saw you on that yacht

17:35.554 --> 17:37.923
I thought you lied to me
about being with your parents.

17:37.956 --> 17:40.761
And then I realized it
was just an old picture.

17:40.793 --> 17:43.129
Why'd you post that?

17:43.162 --> 17:45.264
Because instead of hanging out with me,

17:45.298 --> 17:47.367
my parents bailed to
go sailing with the son

17:47.399 --> 17:49.802
of Dubai's Minister of Foreign Affairs.

17:49.835 --> 17:52.938
They were with someone else's son.

17:52.972 --> 17:55.408
I just didn't want anyone to know.

17:55.440 --> 17:58.244
- Dude, that sucks.
- Yeah.

17:58.277 --> 18:00.212
I guess I just thought
you were sick of slumming it

18:00.245 --> 18:01.480
with your poor friend.

18:01.514 --> 18:02.948
What?

18:02.982 --> 18:05.252
Dude, that's never going to happen.

18:05.284 --> 18:07.119
I don't care how much money you have.

18:07.152 --> 18:08.788
- Really?
- Of course.

18:08.821 --> 18:11.056
Plus, we're the richest family
in Westport.

18:11.090 --> 18:13.059
Literally everyone is beneath me.

18:17.196 --> 18:19.966
Uh, how many tickets
do I need for that drone?

18:19.998 --> 18:21.433
How many tickets do you have?

18:21.466 --> 18:25.071
- Uh, 14.
- 14 tickets.

18:25.103 --> 18:26.606
Well done.

18:29.475 --> 18:31.977
I know it's kind of sad that
he's just giving me things

18:32.011 --> 18:35.514
that I already own...
but it's sadder for him, right?

18:35.548 --> 18:37.450
I'll answer that.

18:37.483 --> 18:38.819
It's sadder for me.

18:38.851 --> 18:40.486
See?

18:40.520 --> 18:41.955
Are we <i>bueno?</i>

18:41.987 --> 18:43.055
<i>Muy bueno.</i>

18:44.823 --> 18:46.192
All right, see you in a couple weeks.

18:46.225 --> 18:47.994
I'll be here.

18:48.026 --> 18:49.662
Is this, like, your full-time job?

18:49.696 --> 18:51.630
Ouch.

18:51.664 --> 18:53.834
Yes. Yes, it is.

18:53.867 --> 18:55.802
And I'm... I'm almost 50 years old.

18:59.439 --> 19:00.474
Go.

19:02.308 --> 19:04.377
Meatloaf, my fave!

19:04.409 --> 19:05.778
The only way this could be better

19:05.812 --> 19:07.379
is if your mom was here, too.

19:07.412 --> 19:09.849
I'm here, you dingbat!

19:09.882 --> 19:12.518
<i>Muy bonita</i>, Mrs. Otto!

19:12.552 --> 19:13.954
You also look really pretty.

19:13.986 --> 19:15.044
Thank you.

19:15.069 --> 19:17.523
I'm your father's date tonight.
We compromised.

19:17.556 --> 19:20.492
First we're gonna go
candle-making... yawn.

19:20.525 --> 19:21.861
Then we're gonna grab dinner

19:21.895 --> 19:24.364
and see The Rock's new movie... groan.

19:24.397 --> 19:26.700
If you don't want to fight
traffic, you can catch the 8:15

19:26.733 --> 19:28.335
at the theater in my basement.

19:28.368 --> 19:30.570
If you're in the mood for an
indie, theater two is showing...

19:30.602 --> 19:32.205
Shut up and eat, Cooper.

19:32.237 --> 19:33.239
That's the stuff.

19:34.773 --> 19:36.577
Here, let me get a picture.
Everyone together.

19:39.611 --> 19:41.348
Everybody smile.

19:44.050 --> 19:45.585
- Did you get it?
- Here, hold on.

